<docs>
	<doc for="OdbcError">
		<summary>
			<para> Collects information relevant to a
 warning or error returned by the data source. This class cannot be
 inherited.
 </para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>This class is created by the <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcDataAdapter"/> whenever an error occurs. 
 Each instance of <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcError"/> created by the <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcDataAdapter"/> is then managed by the
<see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcErrorCollection"/> class, which in turn is created by the 
<see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcException"/> class.</para>
			<para>If the severity of the error is too great, the
 server may close the <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcConnection"/>. However, the user can reopen the connection
 and continue.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para> The following example displays the properties of the <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcError"/>.
 </para>
			<codelink SampleID="Classic WebData OdbcError" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcErrorCollection"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcException"/>
	</doc><doc for="OdbcError.Message">
